	(text "Congratulations!\nYou have successfully pulled the KiCad files from the GitHub repository! Yippee!\nThe next step is to make a change to the schematic and/or the layout and push the changes to a new branch of the repository.\n\nStep-by-Step Instructions:\n1. Change the schematic/layout\n2. Go into the layout editor (The Git plugin interface can only be accessed through the layout editor for reasons)\n3. Launch the Git plugin interface\n4. Create a new branch and name it first_initial-last_name\n5. Make sure all of your changes are unstaged by clicking Rescan\n6. Click Stage Changed to prepare your changes for a Commit\n7. Write in the Commit Message what you changed\n8. Click Sign-Off for formalities\n9. Click Commit\n10. Click Push to push the changes to the branch you just created"
